            "title": "Daily Devotional",
            "value": "%3Cp%3EThe%20story%20of%20the%20lost%20ax%20head%20is%20so%20descriptive%20of%20the%20human%20condition.%20First%2C%20the%20ax%20head%20was%20not%20with%20its%20rightful%20master.%20In%20the%20same%20way%2C%20we%20once%20belonged%20to%20God%2C%20but%20Satan%20stole%20us%20in%20the%20Garden%20of%20Eden%20and%20made%20us%20his%20slaves.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3ESecond%2C%20the%20ax%20head%20was%20in%20the%20wrong%20place.%20It%20should%20have%20been%20out%20doing%20its%20work%2C%20but%20instead%20it%20was%20on%20the%20bottom%20of%20the%20Jordan%20in%20an%20alien%20environment.%20When%20we%20were%20in%20sin%2C%20we%20were%20completely%20submerged%20in%20the%20wrong%20environment-dead%20to%20God%20and%20alienated%20from%20His%20life.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EFinally%2C%20the%20ax%20head%20could%20not%20save%20itself.%20The%20ax%20head%20had%20no%20power%20to%20change%20its%20situation%3B%20thus%2C%20it%20was%20destined%20to%20remain%20stuck%20in%20the%20mud.%20Only%20when%20%22Elisha%20cut%20a%20stick%20and%20threw%20it%20into%20the%20water%22%20(2%20Kings%206%3A6)%20did%20the%20ax%20head%20supernaturally%20begin%20to%20rise%20from%20the%20bottom%20in%20a%20physical%20%22resurrection.%22%20What%20a%20picture%20of%20Jesus'%20death%20and%20resurrection!%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3ENo%20amount%20of%20personal%20desire%20or%20willpower%20can%20lift%20us%20from%20the%20muddy%20quagmire%20of%20sin%20if%20we%20are%20stuck%20fast%20in%20it.%20Only%20Jesus%20can%20deliver%20us.%20We%20then%20belong%20to%20God%2C%20never%20to%20return%20to%20the%20bottom%20again!%20%3C%2Fp%3E%0A"
        },
